What does the following Terraform lifecycle block do?

```hcl
lifecycle {
  create_before_destroy = true
}
```

A PowerShell script manages Windows services but fails intermittently with access denied errors:

```powershell
function Restart-AppServices {
    $services = Get-Service -Name 'MyApp*'
    foreach ($svc in $services) {
        Restart-Service -Name $svc.Name
        Write-Host "Restarted $($svc.Name)"
    }
}
```

The script runs as a scheduled task under a service account. Some services restart fine, others fail. `Get-Service` shows the failing services have `StartType: Automatic (Delayed Start)`. What is the issue and the fix?

choices.D:
Replace getopts with a while/case loop that shifts arguments, using pattern matching for both short (-e) and long (--version) options:
```bash
while [[ $# -gt 0 ]]; do
  case $1 in
    -e|--environment) env="$2"; shift 2 ;;
    --version) ver="$2"; shift 2 ;;
    --dry-run) dry=true; shift ;;
    -v|--verbose) verbose=true; shift ;;
    *) echo "Unknown: $1"; exit 1 ;;
  esac
done
```
Then validate required arguments after the loop.

questions.question:
A Terraform module provisions an AWS VPC with subnets. After adding a new subnet, `terraform plan` shows it wants to destroy and recreate an existing subnet:

```hcl
variable "subnet_cidrs" {
  default = ["10.0.1.0/24", "10.0.2.0/24"]
}

resource "aws_subnet" "main" {
  count         = length(var.subnet_cidrs)
  vpc_id        = aws_vpc.main.id
  cidr_block    = var.subnet_cidrs[count.index]
  availability_zone = data.aws_availability_zones.available.names[count.index]
}
```

The developer adds `"10.0.0.0/24"` to the beginning of the list: `["10.0.0.0/24", "10.0.1.0/24", "10.0.2.0/24"]`. Why does Terraform want to recreate existing subnets and what is the correct fix?
